cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with information spreading in networks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper analyzes the performance of the Push protocol in dynamic networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper studies the impact of network dynamics on the spreading of information. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with network models and their impact on information spreading. 
- cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a protocol for information spreading.
